description: Protesters keep up pressure over disputed elections, as President Lukashenko calls opponents 'rats'.
title: Belarus: Mass protest eclipses defiant Belarus leader's rally
title_page: Belarus: Mass protest eclipses defiant Belarus leader's rally - BBC News
maintext: Speaking to supporters, Mr Lukashenko said he did not like rallies and did not need anyone to defend him. He said it was not his fault that he had to ask for their help. Rejecting calls for a re-run of the presidential election he said Belarus would "die as a state" if that happened.
